=64\u0026u=4832e5abcbc2018121f183a068ef93aa1fd3e357\u0026v=4","profileResourcePath":"/avikchaudhuri","name":"Avik Chaudhuri"},"source":{"__typename":"Issue","__isNode":"Issue","id":"MDU6SXNzdWUxNTkzNzcyMTE="},"willCloseTarget":false,"referencedAt":"2016-06-17T08:39:47Z","innerSource":{"__typename":"Issue","__isReferencedSubject":"Issue","id":"MDU6SXNzdWUxNTkzNzcyMTE=","issueTitleHTML":"Can't filter types with Array.filter","url":"https://github.com/facebook/flow/issues/1915","number":1915,"stateReason":"COMPLETED","repository":{"id":"MDEwOlJlcG9zaXRvcnkyNTg4MDg5MQ==","name":"flow","isPrivate":false,"owner":{"__typename":"Organization","login":"facebook","id":"MDEyOk9yZ2FuaXphdGlvbjY5NjMx"}},"__isNode":"Issue"},"__isNode":"CrossReferencedEvent","id":"MDIwOkNyb3NzUmVmZXJlbmNlZEV2ZW50MTY1ODc5MDAx"},"cursor":"Y3Vyc29yOnYyOpPPAAABVV2EHDgCqTE2NTg3OTAwMQ=="},{"node":{"__typename":"IssueComment","__isIssueTimelineItems":"IssueComment","databaseId":226762840,"viewerDidAuthor":false,"issue":{"author":{"__typename":"User","login":"vkurchatkin","id":"MDQ6VXNlcjI5OTM4NjE="},"id":"MDU6SXNzdWUxMzQyMzkyMDk=","number":1414,"locked":false,"databaseId":134239209},"author":{"__typename":"User","login":"vkurchatkin","avatarUrl":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/2993861?v=4","profileUrl":"https://github.com/vkurchatkin","id":"MDQ6VXNlcjI5OTM4NjE=","name":"Vladimir Kurchatkin"},"id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDIyNjc2Mjg0MA==","body":"Here is my proposal:\n- implement a magic type, that represents result of type check, for example `Typecheck\u003cFoo\u003e`;\n- `Typecheck` is subtype of boolean;\n- `Typecheck` is only allowed to be explicitly used as type of return value of a single-argument function:\n\n``` js\nfunction isNumber(val: mixed): Typecheck\u003cnumber\u003e {\n  if (typeof val === 'number') {\n    return true;\n  }\n\n  return false;\n}\n```\n- if typecheck function returns `true`, that means that argument is of type `Foo`;\n- typecheck function is validated, so you can only return `true` if  `val` is of type `Foo` at this point;\n- typecheck function is only allowed to call other typecheck functions\n\nFor example, `Boolean` can be declared as `\u003cT: {}\u003e(v: ?T): Typecheck\u003cT\u003e`.\n\nFinally, filter function could be declared like this:\n\n``` js\nfilter\u003cT2\u003e(fn: (v: T) =\u003e Typecheck\u003cT2\u003e): Array\u003cT2\u003e\n```\n","bodyHTML":"\u003cp dir=\"auto\"\u003eHere is my proposal:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul dir=\"auto\"\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eimplement a magic type, that represents result of type check, for example \u003ccode class=\"notranslate\"\u003eTypecheck\u0026lt;Foo\u0026gt;\u003c/code\u003e;\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ccode class=\"notranslate\"\u003eTypecheck\u003c/code\u003e is subtype of boolean;\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ccode class=\"notranslate\"\u003eTypecheck\u003c/code\u003e is only allowed to be explicitly used as type of return value of a single-argument function:\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"highlight highlight-source-js notranslate position-relative overflow-auto\" dir=\"auto\" data-snippet-clipboard-copy-content=\"function isNumber(val: mixed): Typecheck\u0026lt;number\u0026gt; {\n  if (typeof val === 'number') {\n    return true;\n  }\n\n  return false;\n}\"\u003e\u003cpre class=\"notranslate\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-k\"\u003efunction\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"pl-en\"\u003eisNumber\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-kos\"\u003e(\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-s1\"\u003eval\u003c/span\u003e: \u003cspan class=\"pl-s1\"\u003emixed\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-kos\"\u003e)\u003c/span\u003e: \u003cspan class=\"pl-v\"\u003eTypecheck\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-c1\"\u003e\u0026lt;\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-s1\"\u003enumber\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-c1\"\u003e\u0026gt;\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"pl-kos\"\u003e{\u003c/span\u003e\n  \u003cspan class=\"pl-k\"\u003eif\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"pl-kos\"\u003e(\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-k\"\u003etypeof\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"pl-s1\"\u003eval\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"pl-c1\"\u003e===\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e'number'\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-kos\"\u003e)\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"pl-kos\"\u003e{\u003c/span\u003e\n    \u003cspan class=\"pl-k\"\u003ereturn\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"pl-c1\"\u003etrue\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-kos\"\u003e;\u003c/span\u003e\n  \u003cspan class=\"pl-kos\"\u003e}\u003c/span\u003e\n\n  \u003cspan class=\"pl-k\"\u003ereturn\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"pl-c1\"\u003efalse\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-kos\"\u003e;\u003c/span\u003e\n\u003cspan class=\"pl-kos\"\u003e}\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cul dir=\"auto\"\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eif typecheck function returns \u003ccode class=\"notranslate\"\u003etrue\u003c/code\u003e, that means that argument is of type \u003ccode class=\"notranslate\"\u003eFoo\u003c/code\u003e;\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003etypecheck function is validated, so you can only return \u003ccode class=\"notranslate\"\u003etrue\u003c/code\u003e if  \u003ccode class=\"notranslate\"\u003eval\u003c/code\u003e is of type \u003ccode class=\"notranslate\"\u003eFoo\u003c/code\u003e at this point;\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003etypecheck function is only allowed to call other typecheck functions\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp dir=\"auto\"\u003eFor example, \u003ccode class=\"notranslate\"\u003eBoolean\u003c/code\u003e can be declared as \u003ccode class=\"notranslate\"\u003e\u0026lt;T: {}\u0026gt;(v: ?T): Typecheck\u0026lt;T\u0026gt;\u003c/code\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp dir=\"auto\"\u003eFinally, filter function could be declared like this:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"highlight highlight-source-js notranslate position-relative overflow-auto\" dir=\"auto\" data-snippet-clipboard-copy-content=\"filter\u0026lt;T2\u0026gt;(fn: (v: T) =\u0026gt; Typecheck\u0026lt;T2\u0026gt;): Array\u0026lt;T2\u0026gt;\"\u003e\u003cpre class=\"notranslate\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-s1\"\u003efilter\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-c1\"\u003e\u0026lt;\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-c1\"\u003eT2\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-c1\"\u003e\u0026gt;\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-kos\"\u003e(\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-en\"\u003efn\u003c/span\u003e: \u003cspan class=\"pl-kos\"\u003e(\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-s1\"\u003ev\u003c/span\u003e: \u003cspan class=\"pl-v\"\u003eT\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-kos\"\u003e)\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"pl-c1\"\u003e=\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-c1\"\u003e\u0026gt;\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"pl-v\"\u003eTypecheck\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-c1\"\u003e\u0026lt;\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-c1\"\u003eT2\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-c1\"\u003e\u0026gt;\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-kos\"\u003e)\u003c/span\u003e: \u003cspan class=\"pl-v\"\u003eArray\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-c1\"\u003e\u0026lt;\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-c1\"\u003eT2\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-c1\"\u003e\u0026gt;\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\u003c/div\u003e","bodyVersion":"f751e9df53eae264b961ef97750dcadbaf1c3ba4aa1cacd937af56d9630ce897","viewerCanUpdate":false,"url":"https://github.com/facebook/flow/issues/1414#issuecomment-226762840","createdAt":"2016-06-17T13:01:26Z","authorAssociation":"CONTRIBUTOR","viewerCanDelete":false,"viewerCanMinimize":false,"viewerCanUnminimize":false,"viewerCanReport":false,"viewerCanReportToMaintainer":false,"viewerCanBlockFromOrg":false,"viewerCanUnblockFromOrg":false,"viaApp":null,"isHidden":false,"minimizedReason":null,"showSpammyBadge":false,"createdViaEmail":false,"authorToRepoOwnerSponsorship":null,"repository":{"id":"MDEwOlJlcG9zaXRvcnkyNTg4MDg5MQ==","name":"flow","owner":{"__typename":"Organi